content: What this app does, it does well. It has a simple, intuitive system for inputting and naving grids. I have had no issues creating simple routes, and the clear interface makes naving on the go a breeze. / Cons are, it is too basic. It lacks offline map support, and the only topo map it uses is open street, which is not a detailed terrain map. It doesn't support manually dropping way points via the map, you cannot browse the map to find the grid at a particular point, and there is not a grid system overlay
